**Description** 




 We currently have a vacancy for a
 **Solution Architect** 
 fluent in English, to offer his/her services as an expert who will be based in Stockholm, Sweden. The work will be carried out either in the company’s premises or on site at customer premises. In the context of the first assignment, the successful candidate will be integrated in the Development team of the company that will closely cooperate with a major client’s IT team on site.










**Your tasks** 









* Support the development and implementation of long-term strategies in the required domain (business process, information, application and technology);
* Define and design as-is and to-be models for the domain;
* Define and develop architecture frameworks, concepts and methods;
* Facilitate development work with architecture support;
* Communicate and explain architecture deliverables;
* Create and maintain models in Sparx Enterprise Architect (or other tools);
* Ensure incorporation of security by design;
* Develop and maintain a comprehensive record of usability requirements and develop relevant IT Products.









**Requirements** 









* University degree with minimum 6 years of experience in IT or non university degree with minimum 12 years of experience in IT;
* Minimum 3 years of experience in enterprise architecture or domain architectures (business process, information, application and technology);
* Experience with Business Information Systems such as PRIME, ECMP, PHE Intranet;
* Experience with SharePoint Online, Power Platform,Power BI and Azure;
* Experience with DevOps practices, CI/CD and automation, as well as programming/ scripting experience;
* Experience in the application of enterprise architecture frameworks and methods (TOGAF);
* Experience in modelling languages and concepts, such as ArchiMate;
* Experience using relevant IT architecture tools, such as Sparx Enterprise Architect;
* Knowledge of design patterns in big data, cloud solutions (Azure) and artificial intelligence and knowledge in public health would be considered an asset;
* A TOGAF (The Open Group Architecture Framework), SABSA (Sherwood Applied Business Security Architecture) or ArchiMate Certification will be considered an asset;
* Excellent command of the English language.



 # Urgent Requirement
